metadata.name: BLEND #189
metadata.description:
BLEND is a minimal generative artwork drawn in a 8px by 8px canvas.
Three pixel square layers of different sizes are drawn on top of each other and blended to create a variety of compositions that range from colourful to monochromatic, from symmetric to unexpected or from pixelated matrices to more blocky shapes.

The token implements 4 random features:
- the color palette, there are 20 of them, each composed of 4 colors
- the colors subset, a range of 2 to 4 colors picked from the palette
- blend mode, one of multiply, overlay, hard light, soft light or color burn
- the order in which the three layers (small, medium, large) are drawn on top of each other

Controls (in live view):
- Press the [s] key on the keyboard to save a PNG file of the token. You'll be asked at which resolution you would like to save file in case you want something bigger then the original 8px by 8px canvas.

metadata.name: Backyard #5
metadata.description:
The house I lived in when I was young was a house with a small backyard with brick walls. I often imagined it in the backyard at the time.
If I grow up and have my own house later, I want to live in a house with a backyard with a dense nature and a view of a vast mountain.
Although I haven't achieved the imagination that I did when I was young yet. I'm so happy because I think it came true in the world of generative art.
I hope you have the backyard that you imagine.

--

Features:
 - Canvas: vertical / horizontal
 - Palette: black / red / green / purple / yellow / blue
 - Highlighted object: tree / flowers / brickwall
 - MountainType: standard / sharp
 - Tree: true / false
 - Flowers: true / false
 - Stars: true / false
 - Fog: true / false
 - Brickwall: true / false
 - Sun or Moon: true / false / supersize
 - After the rain: true / false

--

Press "s" in live mode to download the rendered image as a png file. (2000 x 3000 for vertical, 3000 x 1500 for horizontal)

Made with p5js and passion
By thion, September 2023

metadata.name: Orchard #333
metadata.description:
A natural media rendering of a fruit tree during one of the four seasons. Sometimes, you'll catch it at night - with lights strung on the tree!

The amount of color in spring and fall, snow in winter, fruit on and off the tree will all vary. There are four spring bloom palettes, four trunk colors, and seven types of fruit. 

Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 1000x1000px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

To render a variation at a new size, open live view and append '?size=#' to the end of the URL. The new size may be from 100 to 3,000. This version will not be a 1:1 match to your edition but will have all of the same features.

metadata.name: CityScape: Istanbul #48
metadata.description:
Istanbul is a city that straddles the Bosporus Strait, and lies in both Europe and Asia, with a population of over 15 million residents. Most of the population is located in big iconic hills known as the "Seven Hills of Istanbul". 

   In this project, I tried to capture and interpret the daily life routine of the people who live in these hills with the viewing point from Bosphorus. There are three camera angle possibilities to examine the details in different layers. Also, building types, the slope of the hill, and green area density vary in between those scenarios. There are two time zones: day and night. In the night scene, there is a possibility to obtain the crescent moon which is the symbol of the culture inhabits in these lands.

To save as a high-quality image, open in live view and click yes on the incoming prompt.

Created with p5js

metadata.name: Ignorance is Bliss #33
metadata.description:
"Ignorance is Bliss" is the second collection released as a part of NeoMent's "Abandoned Reality" series.

People often argue over things that are not under their control. But why bother? At the end of the day, your opinion won't change anything unless you have the power to accomplish that change. Of course you can say that you are aguing for "The Truth" or "Justice", but what's the point in your bickering if you aren't going to accomplish anything?
But you can go even further than that, you can choose to ignore global problems completely, live in your own world. One who doesn't know of a problem shan't worry about it - thus, ignorance is bliss. 
Is it right or is it wrong? What's the point in arguing over what I wrote if you won't change anything? All you can do is decide for yourself.
